byline.original: By DAVID BROOKS AND GAIL COLLINS

abstract: Whether it's riots in Athens, denial in Berlin or protests on Wall Street, the political and cultural effects of the financial crisis continue to reverberate.
snippet: Whether it's riots in Athens, denial in Berlin or protests on Wall Street, the political and cultural effects of the financial crisis continue to reverberate.
lead_paragraph: David Brooks: Let me start with the smaller tragedy before I get to the larger one. Gov. Chris Christie will not be running for president. To me this means he will never be president. Those who hesitate the first time they have a chance to run, never win later on.
